article.headline: VA Commonwealth 79, William & Mary 77
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Nick George scored 24 points, Michael Doles had 23 and Virginia Commonwealth used a 7-0 run in overtime to beat William & Mary 79-77. The Rams (9-7, 5-2 Colonial Athletic Association), who tied the game when B.A. Walker hit a 3-pointer with 9 seconds left in regulation, took a 76-71 lead with 2:43 to play in overtime. William & Mary closed to within one twice in the final 1:31, but George hit a field goal with 1:03 left and Renardo Dixon hit a free throw with 12 seconds left. The Tribe (4-12, 0-7) had its best chance to win in regulation, leading 69-62 with 29 seconds left. But Doles made a layup with 18 seconds to go, the Tribe's Nathan Mann missed two free throws with 15 seconds to play, Walker hit two free throws with 12 seconds to go and missed the third, got the rebound and hit the shot to force overtime. Walker added 16 points for the Rams, who were outrebounded 45-35. Corey Cofield led William & Mary with 22 points and 12 rebounds. Nick D'Antoni added 16 points and Mann 15, including a 3-pointer to pull the Tribe to 76-75 in overtime.
